title: V-League: Navy beats Coast Guard
text:
by Kristel Satumbaga
October 18, 2015 Games Today
(The Arena, San Juan)
12:45 p.m. – Army vs UP (V-League)
3 p.m. – PLDT vs Kia (V-League)
5p.m. – IEM vs Navy (Spikers’ Turf)
Philippine Navy waxed hot on offense as it edged Coast Guard, 25-20, 25-23, 25-21, to barge into the win column of the Shakey’s V-League Season 12 Reinforced Conference yesterday at The Arena in San Juan.
Coast Guard’s Samantha Dowson and Cindy Valencia miss the ball against the Navy during their Shakey’s V-League Reinforced Conference at The Arena in San Juan City. (Bob Dungo Jr.)
Veteran Lilet Mabbayad fueled the Lady Sailors’ attacks with 18 points built on 15 kills, two blocks and an ace as they evened their win-loss record to 1-1.
Former Adamson standout Pau Soriano also bolstered Navy’s resolve with 11 points, 10 coming from attacks, even as Hezzymie Acuna and skipper Janet Serafica conspired for 10 points.
Serafica also contributed with 34 excellent sets.
The triumph made up for the Lady Sailors’ weak start in the conference, where they lost to the University of the Philippines (UP) Lady Maroons in four sets last week.
“Mas napatibay lang namin yung teamwork namin ngayon,” said Mabbayad.
Coast Guard fell to a 0-2 hole with none from its players scoring in double figures.
